    <p>E-Book Launch: Voyageurs, Ex­plo­rateurs Et Sci­en­tifiques: The French And Nat­u­ral His­tory In Sin­ga­pore</p>
    <p>Sir Stamford Raf­fles’ ar­rival in Sin­ga­pore in 1819 set in mo­tion a pe­riod of mo­men­tous sci­en­tific con­tri­bu­tions by the French. French ex­plor­ers, nat­u­ral­ists, diplo­mats, traders and no­ble­men vis­ited Sin­ga­pore and played a part in its nat­u­ral his­tory. This book is filled with such sto­ries and records and pro­duced in col­lab­o­ra­tion with the Lee Kong Chian Nat­u­ral His­tory Mu­seum and the Mu­seum na­tional d’His­toire na­turelle in Paris.</p>
    <p>Download at lkc­nhm.nus.edu.sg/pub­li­ca­tions/ books-by-the-mu­seum</p>
    <p>bit.ly/3iWCosT</p>
    <p>Book Lovers Club: Un­cov­er­ing The Hid­den Prej­u­dice That Shapes What We See, Think, And Do by Jen­nifer L. Eber­hardt</p>
    <p>In this on­line event by the Na­tional Li­brary Board, ex­plore ideas by Jen­nifer L. Eber­hardt, an ex­pert on un­con­scious bias and how it af­fects so­ci­ety. Par­tic­i­pants will dis­cover how im­plicit bias can af­fect those who wish to treat all peo­ple equally. To­mor­row, 3pm</p>
    <p>Free, regis­tra­tion</p>
    <p>eventbrite.com</p>


